1. Step: Profile Optimization SOP
Step 1: Profile Setup:
Go to the settings page. https://www.pinterest.com/settings

	•	Profile Photo:
	•	If you have a personal blog/brand, use a personal photo.
	•	If you have a niche site blog, use a simple minimalistic logo.
	•	Example of how I like to set up my logos: (keep it lean & simple) 
	•	Profile Name:
	•	Use your personal name or your site's name.
	•	Add 2-3 main topics you cover.
	•	Pro Tip: If you have enough data, use the KWs of your best-performing boards.
	•	Example: "YourBrandName | Home Decor and Interior Design"
	•	About:
	•	Explain what topics your account covers.
	•	Include 3-5 important KWs you cover.
	•	Don't keyword-stuff.
	•	Website:
	•	Add your main domain like yourbrandname.com
	•	Claim your website under > settings > claimed accounts > websites 
	•	Username:
	•	Use your personal name or your site's name.
	•	Email Address:
	•	Add your domain email here like: contact@yourbrandname.com
Step 2: Convert Your Account to a Business Account
https://www.pinterest.com/settings/account-settings/
Under Account Management, you’ll see a button "convert account".
This gives you access to analytics.

Other:
	•	Add your first boards  
	•	Add relevant board descriptions (with 4-6 relevant annotation keywords)
	•	Save 3-5 relevant pins from others You can do that easily inside your board under "find some ideas for this board" 
	•	Follow other relevant accounts & interact with them (like, comment, save)
	•	If you don't live in the US but would like to get most of your traffic from there, I recommend switching your account to United States.
	•	Under account management > Personal information 

